  <div>
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-wine-700 mb-2">Which food pairings work best with premium Chardonnay?</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-700">Oaked Chardonnays excel with rich preparations like lobster thermidor, roasted chicken with cream sauce, or aged Comté cheese, where the wine's buttery texture complements similar richness in food. Unoaked styles pair beautifully with oysters, seared scallops, or goat cheese salads, allowing both wine and food's delicate flavors to shine. The best Chardonnays have enough acidity to cut through cream-based dishes while possessing sufficient body to match substantial proteins like pork tenderloin or grilled salmon.</p>
